WEBVTT

00:01.600 --> 00:03.880
Well here we are in the admin Council.

00:04.120 --> 00:10.750
One of the questions that gets asked a lot to me is how do you change password a user that forgot the

00:10.750 --> 00:12.520
password and they need a new one.

00:12.520 --> 00:14.590
So how do I get them a new password.

00:14.590 --> 00:17.560
Actually it's pretty simple but you do have to be admin to do it.

00:17.560 --> 00:23.220
So we're in the admin Council go over users here and you will see your users.

00:23.280 --> 00:26.120
So let's say Bonnie forgot her password.

00:26.190 --> 00:29.370
One of the things that we could do is just hover right there for a second.

00:29.370 --> 00:31.920
And as you can see there's reset password.

00:31.920 --> 00:37.620
But if you click you get more stuff tells me a little bit about what she's been up to.

00:37.650 --> 00:39.680
There's your profile down here.

00:39.690 --> 00:41.070
Here is her photo.

00:41.070 --> 00:43.720
Now she doesn't have one and she can do this herself.

00:43.920 --> 00:46.160
But if you want to add a photo Let's go out and do that.

00:46.160 --> 00:47.400
I don't think we've done this.

00:47.400 --> 00:50.100
Click here and select a photo.

00:50.570 --> 00:54.280
Let's use this one right there click open.

00:54.570 --> 00:58.820
Now I want to tell you one thing about these photos Google is very picky about them.

00:58.940 --> 01:02.730
If it's not the right size if it's too big it's going to reject it.

01:02.750 --> 01:05.480
But you'll see that down here and say it rejects it.

01:05.480 --> 01:08.870
If we upload that's when you cross your fingers and there it goes.

01:08.870 --> 01:10.550
It actually happened pretty fast.

01:10.550 --> 01:11.940
Now this button right here means.

01:11.950 --> 01:13.430
Get rid of the photo.

01:13.520 --> 01:15.970
But like I said she can do this herself.

01:16.000 --> 01:22.640
Now as to the password again that's right here you would type in the new password and retype it you'd

01:22.650 --> 01:24.570
see the strength down there.

01:24.570 --> 01:30.460
And I always require my users to change their password the next time they sign in for security.

01:30.570 --> 01:32.220
She would be sent the e-mail.

01:32.220 --> 01:33.080
There you go.

01:33.480 --> 01:34.590
But we're not done.

01:34.590 --> 01:35.840
Let's get out here.

01:35.940 --> 01:36.990
Let's go back.

01:37.790 --> 01:43.200
To our console and go down to more controls right here.

01:43.200 --> 01:45.130
Just click that and go into security.

01:45.890 --> 01:47.860
Password monitoring.

01:47.900 --> 01:55.560
Now if I select that it shows me all my users and their password strength green is good.

01:55.640 --> 01:56.390
It's down to red.

01:56.390 --> 01:57.890
It's bad.

01:57.890 --> 01:59.700
It gives me their password length.

02:00.140 --> 02:02.990
And if Google considers it a good password.

02:02.990 --> 02:08.300
So after they've redone their password I can come here and go where they do type in one two three four

02:08.310 --> 02:09.000
five.

02:09.380 --> 02:10.570
That's not a good password.

02:10.610 --> 02:13.810
I don't see the password but I know it's strength.

02:13.880 --> 02:20.480
Now if you go into basic settings here you can assign a minimum and maximum length.

02:20.480 --> 02:22.550
Now those are the defaults 8 to 100.

02:22.550 --> 02:28.370
And I'd just love to see somebody who typed in a 100 character password I'd be kind of fun.

02:28.520 --> 02:34.360
So you can control that right here in security inside the admin Council.

02:34.370 --> 02:36.200
So if somebody forgets their passwords.

02:36.200 --> 02:37.300
Not really that big of a deal.

02:37.300 --> 02:39.840
It's very easy to reset and you move on.

02:39.890 --> 02:42.870
And here you can even control what kind of passwords they can put in.
